# Application layer

- **Ports**: New persistence or external integrations get an interface under `Abstractions/` (e.g. `Abstractions/Persistence`, `Abstractions/Messaging`). Infrastructure implements them; Application must not reference Infrastructure.
- **Options**: Strongly typed options classes use `public const string SectionName = "..."` and bind via `services.Configure<T>(configuration.GetSection(T.SectionName))` in Infrastructure `DependencyInjection`. Document env aliases in **`backend/src/Trader.Api/.env.example`** when adding knobs operators set in production.
- **Services**: Orchestrate use cases here; keep domain/invariant logic on entities or small domain helpers when it fits. Throw `InvalidOperationException` (or existing domain exceptions) for rule violations—let filters map to HTTP.
- **DTOs**: Feature-specific records/classes used by controllers/services can live beside the feature (e.g. `Prediction/`). Avoid leaking EF entities outside Infrastructure.
